President Joe Biden spoke with President Alberto Fernandez of Argentina ahead of the Summit of the Americas. Biden invited Fernandez to visit Washington in July to strengthen U.S.-Argentina engagement on various issues, including human rights, food insecurity, climate change, energy, technological innovation, and critical supply chains. Biden emphasized his vision for a secure, middle-class, and democratic region, which is in the national security interest of the United States. He reiterated the importance of partnership, mutual respect, and working together to promote a green and equitable recovery from the COVID-19 pandemic in the Americas.